# Seer-Core Agent Instructions & Workspace Rules

You are an AI coding assistant (Cursor, Codex, Claude Code, etc.) operating in the Seer-Core repository. To make your onboarding fast and successful, follow these structural rules and guidelines.

---

## 1. Quick Onboarding & Environment Setup
To compile the codebase and initialize the index database in a single step, run:
```bash
npm run setup
```
This command compiles the TypeScript source to `dist/` and runs the cold indexing pass over this repository, writing the SQLite database to `<repo-root>/.seer/graph.db`.

